<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,499,775]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,499,524]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Crown of head extremely short, posterior margin upturned in middle forming ridge; face wider than long. Ocelli closer to inner margins of adjacent eye than to each other. Forewing venation prominent with fine setae along veins. Male pygofer variable: either elongate, upturned, or truncate with spine-like processes or with marginal blade-like processes. Subgenital plates without macrosetae. Aedeagus symmetrical, aedeagal shaft and dorsal apodeme with processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
